definition: Code used to indicate to which version of the annex 'Biovolumes and Size-classes of Phytoplankton in the Baltic Sea' was used. Recommended use is a SIZRF code from the ICES vocabulary server at http://ices.dk/marine-data/vocabularies/Pages/default.aspx.
The pressure that the oxygen component of an atmosphere sample would have if it alone occupied the same volume at the same temperature as the sample
The initial light-limited slope of a Photosynthesis versus Irradiance (PvI) curve by the phytoplankton using fast-repetition rate (FRR) fluorescence technique with single turnover flash protocol.

The irradiance at the onset of the saturation phase of a Photosynthesis versus Irradiance (PvI) curve (defined as Pmax/alpha) by the phytoplankton using fast-repetition rate (FRR) fluorescence technique with single turnover flash protocol; also called light acclimation parameter.

Electrical resistance measured by resistance thermometers which use sensing elements that consist of a length of fine coiled wire wrapped around a ceramic or glass core. The elements are usually made from a pure material, typically platinum, nickel or copper.
Output voltage from any type of pH sensor
Concentration of dissolved ammonia per unit volume of a water body. Ammonia may be expressed in terms of mass, volume or quantity of substance.

The amount of gaseous nitrogen taken into the particulate phase in a day from a sample of a water body that has been chemically modified by the addition of an aliquot of 15N2-enriched seawater following Mohr et al 2010 (doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0012583).
